    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="167"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <head>No. 162.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">von Schlözer</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 19, 1878</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 18th instant, in which you transmit the sum of 3,000 marks
                    ($705), which has been sent to you by His Majesty the Emperor of Germany for
                    distribution among the suffering German people in the yellow-fever
                    districts.</p>
                <p>It is unnecessary to observe that the people of the United States will fully
                    appreciate the benevolence of His Majesty.</p>
                <p>Informing you that the sum will be distributed in accordance with His Majesty’s
                    desires, and requesting that you will cause to be conveyed to the Emperor the
                    sincerest thanks in the name of the President for his generous gift, I avail,
                    &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
